\layout Subsection

Tolerance Box
\layout Standard
\added_space_bottom smallskip 

\series bold 
\emph on 
Box Keyword
\series default 
\emph default 
: 
\family typewriter 
.<Toleranc>
\layout Standard

This box controls the type and amount of output produced by the program,
 and also the accuracy of the values calculated.
 It uses the following keywords which can be positioned independently within
 the box:
\layout Subsubsection

General settings
\layout Subsubsection*

write_energy_forces
\layout Standard

If present energies, positions and forces of all atoms will be dumped in
 the file 
\family typewriter 
job.31
\family default 
 every time thery are calculated, where 
\family typewriter 
job
\family default 
 is the name/job identifier.
 May be found useful in testing this or other codes.
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
off
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
write_energy_forces
\layout Subsubsection*

write_force
\layout Standard

If present forces on all frozen tip atoms (regions 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

frozen tip
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

tip buffer
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

) will be written to a file 
\family typewriter 
filename
\family default 
 specified.
 This can be used to reduce the noise of the tip force by previously relaxing
 the tip alone and writing any residual forces left (see the next option)
 to the file.
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
filename
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
off
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
write_forces myfile
\layout Subsubsection*
\noindent 
read_force
\layout Standard

If present forces on all frozen tip atoms written to a file 
\family typewriter 
filename
\family default 
 (e.g.
 for an isolated tip) will be read in and subtracted from the current tip
 force to reduce the noise (see the previous option).
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
filename
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: off
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
read_forces myfile
\layout Subsubsection*

do_lateral
\layout Standard

If present, the lateral forces on the tip (in the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $y$
\end_inset 

 directions) will also be calculated
\emph on 
 
\emph default 
and dumped in files 
\family typewriter 
name.TFX
\family default 
 and 
\family typewriter 
name.TFY
\family default 
 alongside with the 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset 


\emph on 
 
\emph default 
force in 
\family typewriter 
name.TFZ
\family default 
\emph on 
.
 
\emph default 
As a default, only the
\emph on 
 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset 

 
\emph default 
force on the tip is calculated.
 Note that presently, only the 
\begin_inset Formula $z$
\end_inset 

-force can be calculated if Image is on, so that the code will stop if do_latera
l is chosen together with the Image box.
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
: none
\layout Standard
\align left 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: off
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
do_lateral
\layout Subsubsection*
\noindent 
shells
\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{Sec::shells}

\end_inset 


\layout Standard
\noindent 
Controls whether shells in regions 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

cluster atoms
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset 

tip atoms
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset 

 are allowed to relax.
 
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Options
\emph default 
:
\series bold 
 
\layout Itemize
\noindent 

\series bold 
moveall - 
\series default 
shells of all atoms are allowed to relax; this option is useful, for instance,
 if one wants to calculate the electronic polarisation alone keeping all
 atoms in their initial positions;
\layout Itemize
\noindent 

\series bold 
frozenall - 
\series default 
all shells are frozen irrespective of whether cores are allowed to move
 or not; this would correspond to the 
\emph on 
frozen core approximation
\emph default 
 if initial positions of shells are the same as for their cores;
\layout Itemize
\noindent 

\series bold 
follow - 
\series default 
only shells of frozen cores are frozen; shells of atoms allowed to move
 will follow them; this is likely to be the most useful and frequently used
 option.
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Default
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
moveall
\layout Standard
\noindent 

\emph on 
Example
\emph default 
: 
\series bold 
shells moveall
